## 📌 Project Overview
This project focuses on analyzing restaurant data to uncover meaningful insights related to customer behavior, pricing patterns, cuisine trends, and geographic distribution.

The goal is to transform raw data into actionable insights using Python-based data analysis techniques.

---

## 🛠 Tech Stack
- Python  
- Pandas  
- NumPy  
- Matplotlib  
- Seaborn  
- Folium  

---

## 📊 Analysis Performed
- Data cleaning and preprocessing  
- Exploratory Data Analysis (EDA)  
- Rating distribution analysis  
- Cuisine-based performance insights  
- Location-based clustering using maps  
- Price vs rating correlation  

---

## 🔍 Key Insights
- Majority of restaurants fall in the **3–4 rating range**  
- **Niche cuisines** often receive higher ratings  
- Restaurants are highly concentrated in **urban areas**  
- Higher ratings generally correlate with **more customer votes**  
- **Premium-priced restaurants** tend to have better ratings  

